  "commentary": "With SPX at 6593.76 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-7562M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+11543M), dealers are currently in buy mode as spot trades above the amplifying 6580 level, creating upward pressure toward the 6605 resistance wall. The breakout regime with -6990M total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy this rally and sell any dips, amplifying moves in both directions rather than providing stabilization. Key battle zone is 6580-6605: below 6580 triggers dealer selling into weakness, while a push above 6605 forces dealer selling into strength as they hedge short gamma positions.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile trending moves with strong momentum in whichever direction breaks first.",
